About Us

Committed to enabling millions to live a dignified life

Over two decades since its inception in 2001, the Wadhwani Foundation, a not-for-profit organization with worldwide presence, has focused on a simple, powerful mission: accelerating job growth and enabling millions to earn a family-sustaining wage and lead a dignified life.

Our History

Since its inception in 2001, the Wadhwani Foundation has been dedicated to accelerating job growth and enabling millions to lead a dignified life. Our journey started in India and has expanded globally, impacting lives across Asia, Africa, and Latin America.

Our Vision

Our vision is to create a world where every individual is empowered to lead a fulfilling and purposeful life, driven by the principles of compassion, integrity, and service to humanity.

Our Mission

We aim to provide comprehensive employability skill development programs that integrate physical, mental, emotional, and spiritual growth. We foster a supportive learning environment where participants can discover their true potential.

Leadership

Led by a team of visionary leaders and experienced educators, our leadership team is guided by a commitment to excellence, innovation, and social responsibility.

Our Approach

We adopt a holistic approach to skill development, recognizing the interconnectedness of physical, mental, and spiritual well-being. Through classroom instruction, practical training, and experiential learning, we provide participants with a comprehensive toolkit for success.

Our Objectives

  • To empower youth and women through employability skill development programs.
  • To foster a culture of innovation, creativity, and entrepreneurship.
  • To promote spiritual awareness and personal growth.
  • To cultivate ethical leadership and social responsibility.
  • To create a supportive community of like-minded individuals committed to positive change.

Our Values

  • Integrity: Commitment to honesty, transparency, and ethical conduct in all interactions.
  • Compassion: Treating others with kindness, empathy, and respect.
  • Excellence: Setting high expectations and delivering exceptional quality.
  • Lifelong Learning: Fostering a culture of continuous learning and personal growth.
  • Service: Serving others with humility, compassion, and selflessness.
  • Spirituality: Embracing diversity and fostering an environment where spirituality is celebrated and respected.
